Hou Hanru Photo: Courtesy of AACThe winners of the 13th Award of Art China (AAC), the Chinese art world's heavyweight accolade, will be revealed on the night of May 27 in Beijing, chairman of the AAC selection panel Hou Hanru announced on Sunday. According to Hou, the selection panel of Barbara Pollack, Dong Bingfeng, Liu Xiaodong, Mami Kataoka, Philippe Pirotte and Zheng Shengtian, held in-depth discussions on the shortlisted candidates vying for the four major awards: Artist of the Year, Young Artist of the Year, Curator of the Year and Art Publication of the Year. Hou said he believes that "the fundamental goal of the award selection is to identify artists who are capable of challenging themselves from a professional, rigorous perspective, and recommend them to the public in a bid to generate discussions that will have greater academic significance." Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Delegation of HUST attends alumni gala in Los AngelesChinese driving Vegas growthHaving fun